A locked frontal cockpit shot inside a gritty, improvised futuristic spaceship. The pilot is seen from the front, perfectly centered and razor-sharp. The cockpit is dense and industrial, with rusted metal panels, scratched surfaces, exposed wiring, blinking indicator lights, analog gauges, and glowing screens.

The pilotâ€™s arms clearly extend forward from their own shoulders and chest. The pilot operates fixed cockpit controls: pressing illuminated buttons, flipping mechanical switches, and adjusting mounted levers.

The spaceship accelerates forward through space. Strong forward thrust is clearly perceived. Outside the cockpit, stars flow rapidly from the front of the ship toward the rear, stretching into elongated light trails. Asteroids and distant spacecraft approach from ahead, pass by the sides of the cockpit, and disappear behind. The cockpit interior remains perfectly sharp and stable.

A rigid, front-facing cockpit view with maximum clarity and temporal consistency. The pilot remains centered inside a worn industrial cockpit.

The pilot continues operating fixed-mounted cockpit controls with precise hand movements.

The ship advances forward at very high speed while performing sharp banking turns. Exterior stars and asteroids clearly move from the front toward the rear of the ship, curving due to the turns. Other spacecraft approach head-on, cross the forward field of view, and streak past behind the cockpit. The sense of forward motion is constant and unambiguous.
